                    "description": "As a Naval Architect for Oceans of Energy, I am responsible for (i) the design and load calculations of the structural components of the offshore floating solar farm and (ii) the detailed design and attachment of the dynamic power cable.\n\nMy daily job includes the conception of various main components of the offshore floating farm, load determination calculations, FEM simulation, and final design optimizations. I am using commercial software such as ANSYS Mechanical and CATIA.\n\nI also have additional tasks such as hydrodynamic simulation of the dynamic power cable and post-processing of data. For these tasks, I mainly use Orcaflex and Python.\n\nMoreover, I am in charge of projects in close collaboration with external companies. \n\nMy personal benefit from working for Oceans of Energy is the fast experience and knowledge I get in being involved in every step, from conceptual design to fabrication. \n\nFinally, I have the chance to go offshore or to help in the fabrication process of the offshore floating solar farm. It allows me to foresee the best adjustments to improve the farm.",
